<issue num="54" status="TC1">
<title>Basic_streambuf's destructor</title>
<section><sref ref="[streambuf.cons]"/></section>
<submitter>Matt Austern</submitter> 
<date>25 Jun 1998</date>

<discussion>
<p>The class synopsis for basic_streambuf shows a (virtual)
destructor, but the standard doesn't say what that destructor does. My
assumption is that it does nothing, but the standard should say so
explicitly. </p>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<p>Add after <sref ref="[streambuf.cons]"/> paragraph 2:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p><tt>virtual&nbsp; ~basic_streambuf();</tt></p>
  <p><b>Effects</b>: None.</p>
</blockquote>
</resolution>

</issue>
